    "Forgetting Target Application Retaining Runtime Privacy Copyright Robustness Toxicity Fairness Capabilities Global weight modification SISA (Bourtoule et al 2021) Exact Item • • • • --M-L Sgnf LOO (Liu and Kalinli 2023) Approx Item • • • • --H-M H GA (Jang et al 2022) Approx Item • • -• --M-L M SeUL (Wang et al 2024) Approx Item • • -• --M H Yao et al (2023) Approx Item • • • • --M H KGA (Wang et al 2023) Approx Item • • • • • • M-L H Eldan and Russinovich (2023) Approx Concept • • -• --H-M H Quark (Lu et al 2022) Approx General • • • • • • H Sgnf Local weight modification PCGU (Yu et al 2023) Approx Concept ----• -H M Task vector (Ilharco et al 2022) Approx Task -----• H-M H F-Learning (Ni et al 2023) Approx Task -----• H-M H DEPN (Wu et al 2023) Approx Item • -----M-L M Pochinkov and Schoots (2023) Approx Task -----• H M Architecture modification EUL (Chen and Yang 2023) Weak/No Item • • • • --H-M M SISA-FC (Kumar et al 2022) Weak/No Item • • • • --L L SISA-A (Kumar et al 2022) Weak/No Item • • • • --M M Zhang et al (2024a) Weak/No Task ---• --M M LEACE (Belrose et al 2023) Weak/No Concept ----• -H-M M Limisiewicz and Mareček (2022) Weak/No Concept ----• -H-M L Leong et al (2023) Weak/No Item ---• --H-M L Input/output modification Gallegos et al (2024) Weak/No Concept ----• -H L SERAC (Mitchell et al 2022) Weak/No General • • • • • • H M MemPrompt (Madaan et al 2022) Weak/No General • • • • • • M L ICUL (Pawelczyk et al 2023) Weak/No General • • • • • • H L Table 2 lists the forgetting datasets used by the surveyed methods.",
    "The \"Forgetting target\" column specifies the forgetting request type (as defined in Sect. 2.2) and a description of the undesired knowledge that has to be unlearned.",
    "Note that some authors select combinations of undesired knowledge and forgetting request types that do not align with real-world scenarios, although their choices might be justified for experimental purposes.",
    "On the one hand, Wu et al (2023) and Borkar (2023) consider PII as items to be forgotten.",
    "However, sensitive information should be treated as a concept to be forgotten, to preclude the model from providing any details compromising privacy."
